    "For instance, in the AlMgCu general-purpose ternary alloy MLP 15, more than 10 million CPU hours were spent on labeling the 141K training data points.",
    "Furthermore, MLPs often struggle to generalize to applications not covered by the training data 5, such as when additional elements are included in materials design or when crystal structures in a broader range of thermodynamic conditions need to be explored.",
    "To further extend the application range of MLPs, efforts have been made to develop \"universal\" or \"fundamental\" models [16] [17] [18] [19] [20] [21], referred to as large atomic models (LAMs), based on extensive density functional theory (DFT)-labeled datasets.",
    "However, the technical approach still requires further exploration, and a LAM-centric ecosystem remains to be established.",
    "The primary factors influencing this exploration process are the methods employed for model training and their subsequent application in various tasks."
